1
00:00:19,040 --> 00:00:20,600
(TINKLING)

2
00:00:24,120 --> 00:00:25,920
-What's wrong?
-Man wounded.

3
00:00:30,480 --> 00:00:31,640
Wake him.

4
00:00:35,400 --> 00:00:38,080
He slipped in the bilge water, Captain,
and fell under the rigger.

5
00:00:38,160 --> 00:00:39,840
His hand...

6
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:42,560
I don't know if he'll survive.

7
00:00:53,160 --> 00:00:54,560
You're a dead man, McGrath.

8
00:00:58,240 --> 00:00:59,360
Same as all the others.

9
00:01:02,600 --> 00:01:04,520
(WOMAN SINGING HAUNTING TUNE)

10
00:01:07,800 --> 00:01:08,800
She's here.

11
00:01:09,720 --> 00:01:11,080
Oh, save our souls.

12
00:01:11,160 --> 00:01:13,480
-I've got to escape!
-Don't go out there! McGrath!

13
00:01:13,560 --> 00:01:16,040
Don't listen, for God's sake.
The siren is a-calling!

14
00:01:32,160 --> 00:01:33,920
(SIREN CONTINUES SINGING)

15
00:01:36,280 --> 00:01:38,920
(McGrath SCREAMING)

16
00:01:51,160 --> 00:01:52,280
Same as all the others.

17
00:01:52,360 --> 00:01:54,600
No sign of a struggle.
No bones or blood.

18
00:01:54,680 --> 00:01:57,880
We're shark bait,
every single one of us.

19
00:01:57,960 --> 00:02:00,000
Stuck on the ocean. Waiting.

20
00:02:00,080 --> 00:02:01,800
Until the wind changes.

21
00:02:01,880 --> 00:02:02,880
(THUMPING)

22
00:02:02,960 --> 00:02:05,520
-What's that?
-That's the creature. It's returned.

23
00:02:12,920 --> 00:02:14,360
Yo ho ho!

24
00:02:16,160 --> 00:02:18,360
Or does nobody actually say that?

25
00:02:18,480 --> 00:02:20,480
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

26
00:03:00,080 --> 00:03:01,680
We made no signal.

27
00:03:01,760 --> 00:03:03,920
Our sensors picked you up.
Ship in distress.

28
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:05,520
-Sensors?
-Yes.

29
00:03:05,600 --> 00:03:08,160
Okay, problem word, 17th century.

30
00:03:08,240 --> 00:03:12,160
My ship automatically...noticed-ish

31
00:03:12,240 --> 00:03:14,680
that your ship was having some bother.

32
00:03:14,760 --> 00:03:16,160
That big blue crate?

33
00:03:16,440 --> 00:03:19,320
That is more magic, Captain Avery.
They're spirits.

34
00:03:19,400 --> 00:03:21,360
How else would they have
found their way below decks?

35
00:03:21,440 --> 00:03:23,720
Well... I want to say
multi-dimensional engineering,

36
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:26,320
but since you had a problem
with sensors I won't go there. Look.

37
00:03:26,400 --> 00:03:31,720
I'm the Doctor, this is Amy, Rory.
We're sailors, same as you. Arr!

38
00:03:34,080 --> 00:03:36,920
Except for the gun thing.
And the beardiness.

39
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:38,720
You're stowaways!

40
00:03:38,800 --> 00:03:40,200
Only explanation.

41
00:03:40,280 --> 00:03:43,760
Eight days we've been stranded here,
becalmed.

42
00:03:44,440 --> 00:03:46,640
You must have stowed away
before we sailed.

43
00:03:46,720 --> 00:03:48,080
BOATSWAIN: What do we do with them?

44
00:03:48,160 --> 00:03:49,920
Oh, I think,
they deserve our hospitality.

45
00:03:51,080 --> 00:03:53,080
(PIRATES LAUGHING)

46
00:03:53,160 --> 00:03:55,280
I suppose laughing like that
is in the job description.

47
00:03:55,360 --> 00:03:56,760
"Can you do the laugh? Check.

48
00:03:56,840 --> 00:03:59,280
"Grab yourself a parrot.
Welcome aboard.”

49
00:03:59,360 --> 00:04:01,880
Stocks are low.
Only one barrel of water remains.

50
00:04:01,960 --> 00:04:04,720
We don't need three more
empty bellies to fill.

51
00:04:04,800 --> 00:04:06,680
-Take the doxy below, to the galley.
-Hey.

52
00:04:06,760 --> 00:04:08,440
Set her to work.
She won't need much feeding.

53
00:04:08,520 --> 00:04:11,600
-Rory, a little help?
-Hey, listen, right.

54
00:04:11,680 --> 00:04:13,160
She's not a doxy.

55
00:04:13,240 --> 00:04:15,440
I didn't mean just tell him off.
Thanks anyway.

56
00:04:16,120 --> 00:04:19,160
If you're lucky, you'll drown
before the sharks can take a bite.

57
00:04:19,240 --> 00:04:20,840
If this is just because
I'm a captain too,

58
00:04:20,920 --> 00:04:22,200
you know, you shouldn't feel threatened.

59
00:04:22,280 --> 00:04:23,640
Your ship is much bigger than mine.

60
00:04:23,720 --> 00:04:25,920
And I don't have the cool boots
or a hat, even.

61
00:04:26,040 --> 00:04:27,160
Time to go.

62
00:04:28,200 --> 00:04:30,240
A bit more laughter, guys?

63
00:04:30,320 --> 00:04:32,640
(PIRATES LAUGHING)

64
00:04:49,280 --> 00:04:52,760
Where are the rest of the crew?
This is a big ship, big for five of you.

65
00:04:52,840 --> 00:04:54,720
I suppose the rest of them
are hiding someplace

66
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:57,320
and they're all going to jump out
and shout boo.

67
00:04:57,400 --> 00:04:58,880
AMY: Boo!

68
00:05:00,240 --> 00:05:01,520
Throw the gun down.

69
00:05:07,760 --> 00:05:10,320
-The rest of you, on your knees.
-Amy, what are you doing?

70
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:12,240
Saving your life.
Okay with that, are you?

71
00:05:12,320 --> 00:05:14,480
Put down the sword.
A sword could kill us all, girl.

72
00:05:14,560 --> 00:05:18,320
Yeah, thanks. That's actually
why I'm pointing it at you.

73
00:05:18,720 --> 00:05:19,720
(SHOUTS)

74
00:05:32,160 --> 00:05:33,600
(GASPS)

75
00:05:36,440 --> 00:05:38,240
(PIRATES WHIMPERING)

76
00:05:44,080 --> 00:05:45,120
(GRUNTS)

77
00:05:45,200 --> 00:05:46,200
(AMY SHOUTS)

78
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:53,600
(SHOUTS)

79
00:05:54,360 --> 00:05:55,360
Yarr!

80
00:05:57,080 --> 00:05:58,080
(SCREAMS)

81
00:06:03,080 --> 00:06:05,720
-You have killed me.
-No way. It's just a cut.

82
00:06:10,560 --> 00:06:14,040
-What kind of rubbish pirates are you?
-One drop. That's all it takes.

83
00:06:14,120 --> 00:06:16,520
One drop of blood
and she'll rise out of the ocean.

84
00:06:16,600 --> 00:06:20,400
Come on. I barely even scratched him.
What are you all in such a huff about?

85
00:06:22,080 --> 00:06:24,040
(SCREAMING)

86
00:06:24,480 --> 00:06:25,480
Ow, ah!

87
00:06:26,320 --> 00:06:27,680
Ow.

88
00:06:31,800 --> 00:06:33,160
Ah, Doctor, what's happening to me?

89
00:06:33,240 --> 00:06:34,720
She can smell the blood on your skin,

90
00:06:34,800 --> 00:06:37,000
-she's marked you for death.
-She?

91
00:06:37,080 --> 00:06:40,680
-A demon, out there in the ocean.
-Okay. Groovy.

92
00:06:40,760 --> 00:06:42,000
So not just pirates today.

93
00:06:42,080 --> 00:06:46,000
We've managed to bagsy a ship
where there's a demon popping in.

94
00:06:46,080 --> 00:06:48,360
Very efficient. I mean,
if something's going to kill you,

95
00:06:48,440 --> 00:06:50,800
it's nice that it drops you
a note to remind you.

96
00:06:52,560 --> 00:06:54,960
(SIREN SINGING)

97
00:06:56,600 --> 00:06:58,160
BOATSWAIN: Quickly now.
Block out the sound.

98
00:06:58,240 --> 00:06:59,720
-What?
-The creature.

99
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:01,880
She charms all her victims
with that song.

100
00:07:01,960 --> 00:07:05,080
Oh, great, so put my fingers in my ears.
That's your plan?

101
00:07:05,160 --> 00:07:09,400
Doctor, come on. Let's go. Let's get
back to the... Oh. Back to the...

102
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:15,680
The music. It's working on him. Look.

103
00:07:15,760 --> 00:07:19,960
You are so beautiful.

104
00:07:20,040 --> 00:07:23,200
-What?
-Oh! No, I love your get-up.

105
00:07:23,280 --> 00:07:26,800
That's great. You should dress
as a pirate more often, huh?

106
00:07:26,880 --> 00:07:29,760
-Hey, hey, cuddle me, shipmate.
-Rory, stop.

107
00:07:29,840 --> 00:07:32,800
Everything is totally
brilliant, isn't it? Huh?

108
00:07:32,880 --> 00:07:36,200
Look at these brilliant pirates.
Look at their brilliant beards.

109
00:07:36,880 --> 00:07:38,240
I'd like a beard.

110
00:07:39,880 --> 00:07:42,000
-I'm going to grow a beard.
-AMY: You're not!

111
00:07:42,080 --> 00:07:43,560
The music turns them into fools.

112
00:07:43,640 --> 00:07:45,040
(LAUGHING)

113
00:07:46,080 --> 00:07:47,440
Oh, my God.

114
00:07:52,280 --> 00:07:55,080
(SIREN SINGING)

115
00:08:22,520 --> 00:08:24,600
(CONTINUES SINGING)

116
00:08:46,560 --> 00:08:49,240
-I have to touch her. Let me touch her!
-Sorry, but he is spoken for.

117
00:08:49,480 --> 00:08:50,480
(SCREECHING)

118
00:08:50,560 --> 00:08:51,560
(AMY SCREAMS)

119
00:08:52,920 --> 00:08:55,240
Amy! Amy.

120
00:08:55,320 --> 00:08:56,840
Everybody into the hold.

121
00:08:57,200 --> 00:08:59,440
(CONTINUES SINGING)

122
00:09:00,520 --> 00:09:02,120
Rory! Come on.

123
00:09:05,280 --> 00:09:07,280
-Come on.
-Hey! Wait!

124
00:09:08,800 --> 00:09:09,800
RORY: Get off!

125
00:09:13,200 --> 00:09:16,000
-AMY: What is that thing?
-The legend. The siren.

126
00:09:16,640 --> 00:09:19,920
Many a merchant ship laden with
treasure has fallen prey to her.

127
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:22,280
She's been hunting us
ever since we were becalmed.

128
00:09:22,360 --> 00:09:25,520
-Picking off the injured.
-Like a shark. A shark can smell blood.

129
00:09:25,600 --> 00:09:29,000
Okay. Just like a shark,
in a dress and singing and green!

130
00:09:29,080 --> 00:09:31,200
A green singing shark
in an evening gown.

131
00:09:31,280 --> 00:09:33,480
-The ship is cursed.
-Yeah, right.

132
00:09:33,560 --> 00:09:36,240
"Cursed” is big with humans.
It means bad things are happening

133
00:09:36,320 --> 00:09:37,960
but you can't be bothered
to find an explanation.

134
00:09:38,040 --> 00:09:39,760
She's the most beautiful thing
I've ever seen.

135
00:09:39,840 --> 00:09:43,040
Actually, I think you'll find she isn't.
We have to leave. Right now.

136
00:09:43,120 --> 00:09:46,080
-That crate of yours really is a ship?
-Well, it's not propelled by the wind.

137
00:09:46,160 --> 00:09:49,840
-Show me. Weigh anchor. Make it sail!
-And the gun's back.

138
00:09:49,920 --> 00:09:51,240
You're big on the gun thing, aren't you?

139
00:09:51,320 --> 00:09:54,720
Freud would say you're compensating.
Ever met Freud? No.

140
00:09:54,800 --> 00:09:57,280
-Comfy sofa.
-Leave the cursed one, Captain.

141
00:09:57,360 --> 00:09:59,200
-The creature can have him.
-Yes, please.

142
00:09:59,280 --> 00:10:00,760
We don't want the siren coming after us.

143
00:10:01,400 --> 00:10:03,240
(PIRATE SCREAMING)

144
00:10:03,320 --> 00:10:05,240
-AMY: It's a leech!
-Everyone out of the water!

145
00:10:08,920 --> 00:10:11,120
It's bitten me, I'm bleeding!

146
00:10:18,040 --> 00:10:20,000
She wants blood.
Why does she want blood?

147
00:10:20,080 --> 00:10:21,880
What were you saying about
leaving the cursed ones behind?

148
00:10:21,960 --> 00:10:23,200
DOCTOR: It's okay. We're safe down here.

149
00:10:23,280 --> 00:10:25,240
No curse is getting through
three solid inches of timber.

150
00:10:26,520 --> 00:10:30,000
-(SINGING)
-Ah. Hello again.

151
00:10:34,040 --> 00:10:36,360
-No! No!
-No!

152
00:10:39,880 --> 00:10:40,880
(SCREAMING)

153
00:10:49,760 --> 00:10:51,880
-"Safe"?
-I have my good days and my bad days.

154
00:10:51,960 --> 00:10:53,520
How did she get in?

155
00:10:53,600 --> 00:10:57,480
Bilge water.
She's using water like a portal. A door.

156
00:10:57,560 --> 00:11:00,040
She can materialise
through a single drop.

157
00:11:00,120 --> 00:11:01,400
We need to go somewhere with no water.

158
00:11:01,480 --> 00:11:03,240
Well, thank God we're not
in the middle of the ocean.

159
00:11:03,320 --> 00:11:04,520
RORY: Did you see her eyes?

160
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:07,080
-Like crystal pools.
-You are in enough trouble.

161
00:11:07,160 --> 00:11:08,960
-The magazine!
-What?

162
00:11:09,040 --> 00:11:10,640
He means the armoury,
where the powder's stored.

163
00:11:10,720 --> 00:11:12,720
-It's dry as a bone.
-Good, let's go there.

164
00:11:12,800 --> 00:11:15,080
-I give the orders.
-Ah.

165
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:17,400
Worried because I'm wearing a hat now?

166
00:11:18,960 --> 00:11:22,120
-Nobody touch anything sharp!
-AMY: Come on, Rory.

167
00:11:27,840 --> 00:11:29,240
-Quickly, man.
-I... I can't.

168
00:11:29,720 --> 00:11:32,520
-The key is gone, Captain.
-How can it have gone?

169
00:11:37,720 --> 00:11:39,480
Someone else had the same idea.

170
00:11:47,320 --> 00:11:48,720
Barricade the door.

171
00:11:49,160 --> 00:11:50,440
Careful of that lantern.

172
00:11:50,920 --> 00:11:54,920
-Every barrel is full of powder.
-Who's been sleeping in my gun room?

173
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:58,040
(MUFFLED COUGHING)

174
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:09,720
You fool! You fool, boy.

175
00:12:10,280 --> 00:12:11,480
What are you doing here?

176
00:12:11,560 --> 00:12:13,720
-BOATSWAIN: Who is he?
-What, he's not one of the crew?

177
00:12:14,480 --> 00:12:15,680
No.

178
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:17,640
He's my son.

179
00:12:22,920 --> 00:12:25,600
What in God's name possessed you, boy?

180
00:12:25,680 --> 00:12:27,040
Your mother will be searching for you.

181
00:12:34,880 --> 00:12:36,000
When?

182
00:12:36,640 --> 00:12:38,040
Last winter.

183
00:12:39,160 --> 00:12:40,320
Fever.

184
00:12:41,120 --> 00:12:42,360
(AVERY SIGHING)

185
00:12:42,440 --> 00:12:43,960
She told me all about you.

186
00:12:44,840 --> 00:12:46,760
How you were a Captain in the Navy.

187
00:12:48,200 --> 00:12:50,360
"An honourable man," she said.

188
00:12:51,720 --> 00:12:53,880
How I would be proud to know you.

189
00:12:58,160 --> 00:13:00,480
-I've come to join your crew.
-I don't want you here.

190
00:13:01,720 --> 00:13:04,240
You can't send me back. It's too late.

191
00:13:04,720 --> 00:13:07,600
-We're a 100 miles from home.
-It's dangerous here.

192
00:13:07,680 --> 00:13:09,040
There is a monster aboard.

193
00:13:11,200 --> 00:13:12,920
She leaves a mark on men's skin.

194
00:13:16,480 --> 00:13:17,680
The black spot?

195
00:13:25,480 --> 00:13:27,720
(COUGHING)

196
00:13:30,640 --> 00:13:33,640
There's nothing wrong with the boy.
He has no scars.

197
00:13:33,720 --> 00:13:37,720
-Yep. Ignore my last theory.
-He has his good days and his bad days.

198
00:13:37,800 --> 00:13:41,000
It's not just blood. She's coming
for all the sick and wounded,

199
00:13:41,080 --> 00:13:43,680
like a hunter chooses
his weakest animal.

200
00:13:43,760 --> 00:13:46,880
Okay, look. He's got fever.
The siren knows it.

201
00:13:46,960 --> 00:13:50,680
Humans. Second-rate. Damage too easily.

202
00:13:50,760 --> 00:13:53,360
It's only a matter of time
before everyone gets bruised.

203
00:13:54,920 --> 00:13:56,920
My ship.
It can sail us all away from here.

204
00:13:57,000 --> 00:13:59,000
You and me, we fetch it. Let's go.

205
00:13:59,080 --> 00:14:01,320
You're not the Captain here, remember?

206
00:14:02,240 --> 00:14:03,840
(SIREN SINGING)

207
00:14:09,120 --> 00:14:11,760
The water's dangerous.
That's how she gets through.

208
00:14:11,840 --> 00:14:13,480
One touch of her hand
and you're a dead man!

209
00:14:13,560 --> 00:14:17,160
-We're all cursed if we stay aboard.
-It's not a curse.

210
00:14:17,240 --> 00:14:19,560
Curse means game over.
Curse means we're helpless.

211
00:14:19,640 --> 00:14:21,880
We are not helpless!

212
00:14:22,960 --> 00:14:24,920
Captain, what's our next move?

213
00:14:26,640 --> 00:14:29,720
-AVERY: Wait with the boy.
-Captain, we're all in danger here.

214
00:14:29,800 --> 00:14:32,840
I said wait and barricade
the door after we've gone.

215
00:14:32,920 --> 00:14:36,120
-Sure you want to go?
-We have to get Rory and Toby away.

216
00:14:36,200 --> 00:14:40,640
She's out there now, licking her lips,
boiling a saucepan, grating cheese.

217
00:14:41,400 --> 00:14:44,280
Okay. Well, remember if you get an itch,
don't scratch too hard.

218
00:14:45,240 --> 00:14:46,760
We've all got to go sometime.

219
00:14:51,840 --> 00:14:55,440
There are worse ways than having your
face snogged off by a dodgy mermaid.

220
00:15:00,920 --> 00:15:03,320
Do you want to draw lots
for who's in charge, then?

221
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:06,200
Darkness. Demon.

222
00:15:07,480 --> 00:15:10,320
-You can have first go.
-(AVERY LAUGHS)

223
00:15:20,280 --> 00:15:22,040
-Nearly.
-Phew!

224
00:15:29,480 --> 00:15:31,640
-By all the...
-Let me stop you there.

225
00:15:31,720 --> 00:15:32,880
Bigger on the inside.

226
00:15:32,960 --> 00:15:35,440
Don't mind, do you, if we just
skip to the end of that moment?

227
00:15:35,520 --> 00:15:38,800
Oh, and sorry I lied, by the way,
when I said yours was bigger.

228
00:15:38,880 --> 00:15:42,000
Kitchen that way. Choice of bathrooms
there, there, there.

229
00:15:43,240 --> 00:15:45,200
(COUGHING)

230
00:15:46,360 --> 00:15:47,840
What's wrong?

231
00:15:48,840 --> 00:15:51,120
The most beautiful thing
you've ever seen.

232
00:15:52,080 --> 00:15:54,200
Oh, tell me I didn't really say that.

233
00:15:57,200 --> 00:15:58,200
What's going on?

234
00:15:58,280 --> 00:16:00,080
We're not staying here
to mollycoddle the boy.

235
00:16:00,160 --> 00:16:02,400
The Captain's gone soft.
It's time for us to leave.

236
00:16:07,600 --> 00:16:08,600
What's this do?

237
00:16:08,680 --> 00:16:11,000
That does very, very complicated.
That does sophisticated.

238
00:16:11,080 --> 00:16:12,840
That does whoa, amazing!

239
00:16:12,920 --> 00:16:16,400
And that does whizz, bang,
far too technical to explain!

240
00:16:16,480 --> 00:16:18,320
-Wheel?
-Atom accelerator.

241
00:16:18,400 --> 00:16:21,880
-It steers the thing.
-No! Sort of. Yes.

242
00:16:21,960 --> 00:16:26,320
Wheel. Telescope. Astrolabe. Compass.
A ship's a ship.

243
00:16:26,400 --> 00:16:27,600
Good man.

244
00:16:30,040 --> 00:16:34,680
He told you to wait, you dog.
He's your Captain. A naval officer.

245
00:16:34,760 --> 00:16:36,640
You're honour-bound to do
as he tells you.

246
00:16:36,720 --> 00:16:38,840
Honour-bound?
Do you know what kind of ship this is?

247
00:16:38,920 --> 00:16:41,640
-Do you know what your father does?
-Don't listen to him, Toby.

248
00:16:42,400 --> 00:16:45,240
We sail under the black flag.
The Jolly Roger.

249
00:16:46,760 --> 00:16:47,960
Liar!

250
00:16:48,200 --> 00:16:50,600
-He's no wicked pirate!
-Oh, you think so?

251
00:16:51,440 --> 00:16:55,400
I've seen your father gun down
a thousand innocent men.

252
00:17:00,320 --> 00:17:02,520
This is how the professionals do it.

253
00:17:03,200 --> 00:17:05,440
(ENGINE STALLING)

254
00:17:06,920 --> 00:17:10,320
Um, it's stuck. Not responding.

255
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:12,920
-Becalmed?
-Mmm-hmm. Apparently. That's new.

256
00:17:15,520 --> 00:17:17,360
-You had to gloat, didn't you?
-I'm not gloating.

257
00:17:17,440 --> 00:17:19,960
I saw that look just now.
"Ha ha. His ship is rubbish."

258
00:17:20,040 --> 00:17:21,640
-True.
-Mmm-hmm.

259
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:25,160
Get what treasure you can.
I'll meet you in the rowboat.

260
00:17:25,240 --> 00:17:28,000
You're going to remain at your post.

261
00:17:29,040 --> 00:17:31,920
I am not playing games with you, boy.
You put that down.

262
00:17:32,320 --> 00:17:35,360
One more step and I'll use this,
you blackguard.

263
00:17:35,440 --> 00:17:37,440
You don't know how to
fight with a cutlass, boy.

264
00:17:38,640 --> 00:17:39,920
Don't need to, do I?

265
00:17:40,800 --> 00:17:41,800
Ah!

266
00:17:46,320 --> 00:17:48,280
I can't get a lock on the plane.

267
00:17:48,360 --> 00:17:49,840
-The what?
-The space we travel in.

268
00:17:49,920 --> 00:17:53,600
The ocean. Sort of ocean but not water.
The Tardis can't see.

269
00:17:53,680 --> 00:17:55,760
It's sulking because it thinks
the space doesn't exist.

270
00:17:55,840 --> 00:17:58,280
Without a plane to lock onto
we're not going anywhere.

271
00:17:58,360 --> 00:17:59,400
I'm confused.

272
00:17:59,480 --> 00:18:01,320
Yeah, well, it's a big club.
We should get t-shirts.

273
00:18:01,400 --> 00:18:03,320
(EXPLOSIVE RUMBLING)

274
00:18:07,320 --> 00:18:08,680
What's happening?

275
00:18:11,840 --> 00:18:15,800
-You little swabber!
-Congratulations. Made it to the menu.

276
00:18:15,880 --> 00:18:18,520
-Probably shouldn't go out there now.
-You scurvy ape!

277
00:18:18,800 --> 00:18:21,520
Don't shoot!
The powder will blow and kill us all.

278
00:18:22,760 --> 00:18:24,160
Mulligan, what are you doing?

279
00:18:27,880 --> 00:18:29,360
No honour among pirates.

280
00:18:36,880 --> 00:18:38,040
All right. She's had her little sulk.

281
00:18:38,120 --> 00:18:40,080
Now she's heading for
the full-on screaming tantrum.

282
00:18:40,160 --> 00:18:41,920
-Can you fix it?
-Oh!

283
00:18:42,000 --> 00:18:44,360
The parametric engines are jammed.
Orthogonal vector's gone.

284
00:18:44,440 --> 00:18:46,080
-I'm almost out of ideas.
-Almost?

285
00:18:46,160 --> 00:18:48,360
Well, we could try stroking her
and singing her a song.

286
00:18:48,440 --> 00:18:51,600
-Will that help?
-Hard to say. Never has before.

287
00:18:52,920 --> 00:18:54,200
I've lost control of her.

288
00:18:54,400 --> 00:18:57,120
She's about to dematerialise.
We could end up anywhere!

289
00:18:57,200 --> 00:18:59,360
-That sounds bad.
-Yes, it is!

290
00:19:00,680 --> 00:19:01,960
Out! Now!

291
00:19:03,320 --> 00:19:05,480
Abandon ship! Abandon ship!

292
00:19:07,400 --> 00:19:08,800
(WHOOSHING)

293
00:19:18,800 --> 00:19:21,360
Okay. Okay. Oh, okay.

294
00:19:21,440 --> 00:19:24,480
Tardis runs off on its own.
That's a bit of a new one.

295
00:19:24,560 --> 00:19:26,600
Bang goes our only hope
of getting them out of here.

296
00:19:26,680 --> 00:19:29,160
Not much of a Captain
without a ship, are you?

297
00:19:37,200 --> 00:19:38,200
Mulligan?

298
00:19:38,520 --> 00:19:41,040
What are you doing? This is mutiny.

299
00:19:41,400 --> 00:19:43,040
She doesn't want me.

300
00:19:43,120 --> 00:19:46,120
She only wants Toby
and the scrawny looking fellow.

301
00:19:48,120 --> 00:19:49,920
He's got the last of the supplies.
We should go after him.

302
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:52,280
Never mind the damned supplies.
What about my treasure?

303
00:19:55,960 --> 00:19:58,200
(FIRING)

304
00:19:58,280 --> 00:19:59,280
(BULLETS RICOCHETING)

305
00:20:00,920 --> 00:20:02,200
Don't get injured.

306
00:20:02,720 --> 00:20:03,880
Don't get injured!

307
00:20:12,360 --> 00:20:14,520
AVERY: Come out of there,
you mutinous dog!

308
00:20:19,080 --> 00:20:20,960
(SIREN SINGING)

309
00:20:28,640 --> 00:20:31,600
She's inside. She's come for Mulligan.

310
00:20:32,240 --> 00:20:33,920
(MULLIGAN SCREAMING)

311
00:20:48,120 --> 00:20:49,880
No water in here. How did she take him?

312
00:20:50,440 --> 00:20:52,800
You said she uses water like a door.
That's how she enters a room.

313
00:20:59,760 --> 00:21:00,760
I was wrong.

314
00:21:02,520 --> 00:21:04,400
Please ignore all my theories
up to this point.

315
00:21:04,480 --> 00:21:05,520
What? Again?

316
00:21:06,720 --> 00:21:08,480
We're all in danger.

317
00:21:09,480 --> 00:21:11,000
The water's not how she's getting in.

318
00:21:11,880 --> 00:21:13,360
When we were down in the hold,
think what happened.

319
00:21:13,440 --> 00:21:16,200
-You, me, Amy, Rory, leeches.
-She sprang from the water.

320
00:21:16,280 --> 00:21:19,720
Yes, only when it grew still!
Still water. Nature's mirror.

321
00:21:20,240 --> 00:21:22,640
-So... You mean?
-Yes. Not water.

322
00:21:24,920 --> 00:21:26,280
Reflection.

323
00:21:35,720 --> 00:21:37,960
The siren legend. The curse.

324
00:21:38,040 --> 00:21:40,800
-You said curses weren't real.
-Folklore springs from truth.

325
00:21:40,880 --> 00:21:42,720
She attacks ships filled with treasure.

326
00:21:42,800 --> 00:21:44,720
Where else do you get
a perfect reflection?

327
00:21:44,800 --> 00:21:46,400
-Polished metal.
-Hmm.

328
00:21:50,960 --> 00:21:52,400
We must warn them!

329
00:22:08,760 --> 00:22:12,320
-Amy! Open the door!
-Toby, open the door!

330
00:22:13,600 --> 00:22:14,720
Toby!

331
00:22:14,800 --> 00:22:16,840
-Open the door.
-Toby!

332
00:22:18,600 --> 00:22:20,400
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

333
00:22:34,680 --> 00:22:37,960
We've got to destroy every reflection.
Gold, Silver, Glass.

334
00:22:38,040 --> 00:22:39,680
She could spring from any of them.

335
00:22:47,080 --> 00:22:49,560
Oh, yes, yes. I know, I know.
Very bad luck to break it.

336
00:22:49,640 --> 00:22:50,920
But look at it this way.

337
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:53,760
There's a stroppy, homicidal mermaid
trying to kill all.

338
00:22:54,640 --> 00:22:56,400
-How much worse can things get?
-Yep.

339
00:22:57,400 --> 00:22:58,560
Help me lug this lot out.

340
00:22:58,640 --> 00:23:00,320
-Where are we taking it?
-The ocean.

341
00:23:00,400 --> 00:23:02,080
No! No.

342
00:23:02,800 --> 00:23:04,560
This is the treasure
of the Mogul of India.

343
00:23:04,640 --> 00:23:07,400
Oh, good. For a moment there,
I thought it was yours.

344
00:23:07,480 --> 00:23:09,080
Doctor! Wait.

345
00:23:09,920 --> 00:23:11,000
Must we do this?

346
00:23:11,080 --> 00:23:14,760
Any reflection, any mirror
and the siren will attack.

347
00:23:14,840 --> 00:23:16,640
We have to protect Rory and Toby.

348
00:23:18,080 --> 00:23:19,840
Go and get the crown from the storeroom.

349
00:23:41,240 --> 00:23:43,080
(SIREN SINGING)

350
00:23:52,160 --> 00:23:53,480
Just wait?

351
00:23:54,160 --> 00:23:56,640
-Not my most dynamic plan, I realise.
-Tardis.

352
00:23:56,720 --> 00:23:58,480
-It's been towed.
-What?

353
00:23:59,280 --> 00:24:00,920
Sorry.
We might be stuck here for a while.

354
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:03,200
Oh, so you're saying that we should
all just wait here below?

355
00:24:03,280 --> 00:24:05,560
The sea is still calm, like a mirror.

356
00:24:05,640 --> 00:24:07,520
If you go out on deck,
she'll rise up and attack you.

357
00:24:07,600 --> 00:24:09,520
It's okay. The calm won't last forever.

358
00:24:09,600 --> 00:24:11,760
When the wind picks up,
we'll all set sail.

359
00:24:11,840 --> 00:24:13,960
Until it does,
you have to hide down here.

360
00:24:17,560 --> 00:24:19,600
(SIREN SINGING)

361
00:24:29,760 --> 00:24:31,920
I'm sorry about your mother.

362
00:24:33,480 --> 00:24:34,600
You miss her a lot?

363
00:24:35,760 --> 00:24:38,120
Three years. No word from you.

364
00:24:39,040 --> 00:24:40,680
-Toby...
-You promised her.

365
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:43,880
You promised you'd come home.

366
00:24:45,120 --> 00:24:46,600
And she believed you would,

367
00:24:48,160 --> 00:24:49,800
right up until the day she died.

368
00:24:55,520 --> 00:24:56,760
What made you do it?

369
00:24:57,280 --> 00:24:59,600
What made you turn pirate?

370
00:25:02,320 --> 00:25:03,640
Get some sleep now.

371
00:25:12,560 --> 00:25:14,920
FEMALE VOICE: It's fine.
You're doing fine.

372
00:25:15,920 --> 00:25:18,000
Just stay calm.

373
00:25:33,640 --> 00:25:35,800
It's not one star, it's two.

374
00:25:37,760 --> 00:25:39,200
The Dog Star.

375
00:25:40,640 --> 00:25:42,360
Sirius. Binary system.

376
00:25:42,440 --> 00:25:44,200
I use it to navigate the oceans.

377
00:25:46,520 --> 00:25:48,040
I've travelled far, like you.

378
00:25:49,040 --> 00:25:50,800
Space can be very lonely.

379
00:25:52,200 --> 00:25:55,160
The greatest adventure is having
someone share it with you.

380
00:25:57,000 --> 00:25:59,200
If we get out of this,
I'll take him back to England.

381
00:25:59,280 --> 00:26:00,720
He can't stay with me.

382
00:26:02,160 --> 00:26:03,520
I'm not the father he needs.

383
00:26:05,560 --> 00:26:07,160
Who are you, Henry Avery?

384
00:26:09,200 --> 00:26:11,880
Respected naval officer,
wife and child at home.

385
00:26:13,120 --> 00:26:14,560
How did you end up here,

386
00:26:14,640 --> 00:26:17,480
wandering the oceans
with a band of rogues?

387
00:26:22,120 --> 00:26:23,800
I've set my course now.

388
00:26:25,600 --> 00:26:27,120
Nothing I can do to alter it.

389
00:26:28,800 --> 00:26:31,200
People stared at it for centuries
and never knew.

390
00:26:33,000 --> 00:26:34,680
Things can suddenly change,

391
00:26:36,440 --> 00:26:37,920
when you're least expecting.

392
00:27:01,880 --> 00:27:03,080
-Doctor, um...
-Shh.

393
00:27:05,560 --> 00:27:06,720
What can you see?

394
00:27:08,800 --> 00:27:10,760
Feels like something's out there,

395
00:27:11,720 --> 00:27:13,360
staring straight at me.

396
00:27:14,640 --> 00:27:16,760
(THUNDERCLAP)

397
00:27:20,840 --> 00:27:23,120
Man the sails!

398
00:27:27,320 --> 00:27:31,760
To the rigging, you dogs!
Let go the sails. Avast ye!

399
00:27:34,440 --> 00:27:36,760
Put the bunt into the slack
of the clews.

400
00:27:37,440 --> 00:27:39,600
I swear he's making half this stuff up.

401
00:27:39,680 --> 00:27:42,720
Well, we're going to need
some kind of phrase book.

402
00:27:43,200 --> 00:27:44,200
(GRUNTING)

403
00:27:47,280 --> 00:27:48,640
Toby!

404
00:27:48,720 --> 00:27:49,720
Find my coat.

405
00:27:51,360 --> 00:27:53,360
My compass is inside it, boy.

406
00:27:54,600 --> 00:27:56,560
Heave ho, you bilge rats.

407
00:27:57,360 --> 00:27:59,440
"Rats" was all I could hear.

408
00:28:30,440 --> 00:28:32,640
(SIREN SINGING)

409
00:28:43,920 --> 00:28:45,440
Don't let her take you!

410
00:28:46,120 --> 00:28:47,880
(SINGING)

411
00:28:56,360 --> 00:28:57,560
No!

412
00:28:57,640 --> 00:28:58,880
(TOBY SCREAMING)

413
00:28:58,960 --> 00:29:00,400
No!

414
00:29:00,480 --> 00:29:01,840
Hang on!

415
00:29:07,480 --> 00:29:08,520
No!

416
00:29:10,120 --> 00:29:12,040
I'm sorry, I'm sorry!

417
00:29:13,360 --> 00:29:15,400
You couldn't give up the gold,
could you?

418
00:29:15,480 --> 00:29:17,240
That's why you turned pirate!

419
00:29:17,560 --> 00:29:20,400
Your commission, your wife, your son!

420
00:29:21,200 --> 00:29:24,080
Just how much
is that treasure worth to you, man?

421
00:29:25,760 --> 00:29:26,760
(GROANING)

422
00:29:26,880 --> 00:29:28,720
Rory! Rory!

423
00:29:28,800 --> 00:29:33,320
-Rory!
-I can't see him. Doctor, I'm going in!

424
00:29:37,200 --> 00:29:40,600
He's drowning. He's drowning!
You go in after him, you'll drown too.

425
00:29:41,480 --> 00:29:42,880
There's only one thing
that can save him now.

426
00:29:42,960 --> 00:29:45,040
-What are you talking about?
-The siren.

427
00:29:45,520 --> 00:29:47,720
The siren, she wants him.
We have to release her.

428
00:29:48,400 --> 00:29:49,840
Doctor, no.

429
00:29:55,000 --> 00:29:56,000
No!

430
00:29:59,760 --> 00:30:01,720
He's drowning. Go find him!

431
00:30:09,320 --> 00:30:10,880
What did you do?

432
00:30:10,960 --> 00:30:13,840
-If he stays in there, he'll die.
-But she'll destroy him.

433
00:30:13,920 --> 00:30:17,000
That thing isn't just a ravenous hunter.
It's intelligent.

434
00:30:17,080 --> 00:30:18,760
We can reason with it. And maybe,

435
00:30:18,840 --> 00:30:21,400
just maybe,
they're still alive somewhere.

436
00:30:22,040 --> 00:30:24,640
-We have to follow her.
-Are you mad?

437
00:30:24,720 --> 00:30:28,760
If we ever want to see them again,
we have to let the siren take us.

438
00:30:29,360 --> 00:30:30,760
We'll prick our fingers.

439
00:30:32,440 --> 00:30:33,880
All agreed?

440
00:30:35,160 --> 00:30:36,920
-Yeah?
-Aye.

441
00:30:38,160 --> 00:30:39,360
-Aye.
-Aye!

442
00:30:54,280 --> 00:30:56,400
(SINGING)

443
00:31:14,440 --> 00:31:15,560
AMY: Where are we?

444
00:31:17,360 --> 00:31:18,600
We haven't moved.

445
00:31:19,440 --> 00:31:21,640
We're in exactly
the same place as before.

446
00:31:23,840 --> 00:31:27,680
-We're on a ghost ship.
-No. It's real.

447
00:31:28,520 --> 00:31:30,360
A space ship trapped in a temporal rift.

448
00:31:30,960 --> 00:31:33,280
How can two ships be in the same place?

449
00:31:33,840 --> 00:31:36,360
Not the same. Two planes, two worlds.

450
00:31:36,880 --> 00:31:39,520
Two cars parked in the same space.

451
00:31:39,600 --> 00:31:42,000
There are lots of different universes
nested inside each other.

452
00:31:42,080 --> 00:31:46,640
Now and again they collide.
And you can step from one to the other.

453
00:31:47,400 --> 00:31:49,520
Okay. I think I understand.

454
00:31:49,600 --> 00:31:51,760
Good. 'Cause it's not like that at all,
but if that helps.

455
00:31:51,840 --> 00:31:52,840
Thanks.

456
00:31:52,920 --> 00:31:56,080
All the reflections have
suddenly become gateways.

457
00:32:04,840 --> 00:32:08,040
Ever look in a mirror and think
you're seeing a whole other world?

458
00:32:09,200 --> 00:32:11,280
Well, this time it's not an illusion.

459
00:32:12,160 --> 00:32:14,120
(ALARM SOUNDING)

460
00:32:18,600 --> 00:32:20,560
-The signal.
-Yes?

461
00:32:21,880 --> 00:32:23,840
-The distress call.
-Uh-huh.

462
00:32:25,560 --> 00:32:27,440
There was a second ship here
all the time.

463
00:32:27,520 --> 00:32:28,560
(SIREN SINGING)

464
00:32:28,640 --> 00:32:30,760
And the siren is on board.

465
00:32:39,040 --> 00:32:40,160
Dead.

466
00:33:01,560 --> 00:33:05,320
You were right, there was something
staring at us the whole time.

467
00:33:05,400 --> 00:33:07,480
How long has this ship
been marooned here?

468
00:33:07,560 --> 00:33:10,040
Long enough for the Captain
to have run out of grog.

469
00:33:10,120 --> 00:33:13,200
I don't understand. If this is the
Captain, then what's the siren?

470
00:33:13,280 --> 00:33:14,640
Same as us.

471
00:33:15,240 --> 00:33:16,560
A stowaway.

472
00:33:16,640 --> 00:33:17,760
She killed it?

473
00:33:19,800 --> 00:33:21,000
Human bacteria.

474
00:33:21,280 --> 00:33:24,000
-What?
-A virus. From our planet.

475
00:33:24,080 --> 00:33:25,800
Airborne, travelling through the portal.

476
00:33:26,600 --> 00:33:29,160
That's what killed it.
Didn't get its jabs.

477
00:33:30,760 --> 00:33:33,080
-Ugh! Look.
-What is it?

478
00:33:33,160 --> 00:33:34,400
Sneeze!

479
00:33:34,960 --> 00:33:36,720
Alien bogies.

480
00:33:51,680 --> 00:33:53,040
(SENSORS BEEPING)

481
00:33:53,640 --> 00:33:55,400
(SIREN SINGING)

482
00:34:04,880 --> 00:34:07,320
-McGrath! He's one of my men.
-AMY: He's still breathing.

483
00:34:07,680 --> 00:34:09,320
My entire crew is here.

484
00:34:09,400 --> 00:34:11,680
-Toby!
-Rory!

485
00:34:11,760 --> 00:34:13,000
The Tardis!

486
00:34:15,520 --> 00:34:17,400
-We have to get him out of here.
-Wait!

487
00:34:19,000 --> 00:34:20,400
His fever's gone.

488
00:34:20,520 --> 00:34:21,520
Ah.

489
00:34:24,160 --> 00:34:26,600
-He looks so well.
-She's keeping him alive.

490
00:34:27,360 --> 00:34:31,520
His brain is still active but all
its cellular activity is suspended.

491
00:34:31,600 --> 00:34:34,640
It's not a curse, it's a tissue sample.

492
00:34:34,720 --> 00:34:36,760
Why get samples of people
you are about to kill?

493
00:34:36,840 --> 00:34:38,080
Help me get him up?

494
00:34:41,600 --> 00:34:43,560
(SENSOR BEEPING QUICKLY, SIREN SINGING)

495
00:34:43,640 --> 00:34:45,080
She's coming.

496
00:34:46,080 --> 00:34:47,080
(GROANING)

497
00:35:02,480 --> 00:35:04,080
(SINGING)

498
00:35:09,080 --> 00:35:11,200
-Anaesthetic.
-AVERY: What?

499
00:35:12,000 --> 00:35:14,040
Her music. The song.

500
00:35:14,920 --> 00:35:18,200
So she anaesthetises people
and then puts their body in stasis.

501
00:35:21,120 --> 00:35:22,440
Avery. No!

502
00:35:22,960 --> 00:35:24,400
(SCREECHING)

503
00:35:33,120 --> 00:35:34,520
(DOCTOR SNEEZING)

504
00:35:39,000 --> 00:35:41,240
Fire. That's new. Uh...

505
00:35:41,320 --> 00:35:44,640
What does fire do? Burn? Yes.
Destroy. What else?

506
00:35:45,200 --> 00:35:49,520
Sterilise! (STAMMERING) I sneezed.
I brought germs in.

507
00:35:54,200 --> 00:35:56,120
Amy, stop. Don't interfere.
Don't touch him.

508
00:35:56,200 --> 00:35:59,040
Anaesthetic, tissue sample, screen,
sterile working conditions.

509
00:35:59,120 --> 00:36:00,160
Ignore all my previous theories!

510
00:36:00,240 --> 00:36:02,000
Yeah? Well, we stopped
paying attention a while back.

511
00:36:02,080 --> 00:36:04,120
She's not a killer at all.
She's a doctor!

512
00:36:09,520 --> 00:36:12,720
This is an automated sick bay.
It's teleporting everyone on board.

513
00:36:12,800 --> 00:36:15,200
The crew are dead and so the sick bay
has had nothing to do.

514
00:36:15,280 --> 00:36:17,600
It's been looking after humanity
whilst it's been idle.

515
00:36:18,400 --> 00:36:22,760
Look at her. A virtual doctor!
Able to sterilise a whole room.

516
00:36:22,840 --> 00:36:25,040
-Able to burn your face off.
-She's just an interface.

517
00:36:25,120 --> 00:36:27,160
Seeped through the join
between the planes.

518
00:36:27,240 --> 00:36:28,480
Broadcast in our world.

519
00:36:29,200 --> 00:36:32,360
Protean circuitry means
she can change her form.

520
00:36:32,440 --> 00:36:38,040
And become a human doctor for humans.
Oh, sister, you are good!

521
00:36:40,720 --> 00:36:42,400
(SCREECHING)

522
00:36:43,400 --> 00:36:44,600
She won't let us take them.

523
00:36:44,680 --> 00:36:46,840
She's keeping them alive but
she doesn't know how to heal them.

524
00:36:47,280 --> 00:36:49,560
I'm his wife, for God's sake!
Why can't I touch him?

525
00:36:51,520 --> 00:36:52,520
Tell her, Amy.

526
00:36:53,400 --> 00:36:54,440
Show her your ring.

527
00:36:54,520 --> 00:36:55,840
She may be virtual
but she's intelligent.

528
00:36:55,920 --> 00:36:58,360
You can't do anything
without her consent. Come on!

529
00:36:58,840 --> 00:36:59,840
Sophisticated girl like you,

530
00:36:59,920 --> 00:37:01,760
that must be somewhere
in your core program.

531
00:37:03,600 --> 00:37:06,440
Look. He's very ill, okay?
I just want to look after him.

532
00:37:09,000 --> 00:37:11,240
Why won't you let me near my husband?

533
00:37:22,480 --> 00:37:25,640
Consent form. Sign it.
Put your hand in the light.

534
00:37:25,720 --> 00:37:27,920
Rory's sick.
You have to take full responsibility.

535
00:37:38,600 --> 00:37:39,680
(GASPING)

536
00:37:41,080 --> 00:37:42,760
He can't breathe. Turn it back on.

537
00:37:46,520 --> 00:37:48,320
What do we do?
I can't just leave him here.

538
00:37:48,400 --> 00:37:49,640
He'll die if you take him out.

539
00:37:53,120 --> 00:37:54,320
Rory? Rory, wake up.

540
00:37:58,040 --> 00:37:59,760
-Where am I?
-DOCTOR: You're in a hospital.

541
00:38:00,480 --> 00:38:02,000
If you leave, you might die.

542
00:38:03,440 --> 00:38:06,560
But if you don't,
you'll have to stay forever.

543
00:38:07,520 --> 00:38:09,640
You're saying
that if I don't get up now...

544
00:38:09,720 --> 00:38:10,920
You can never leave.

545
00:38:11,400 --> 00:38:14,840
-The siren will keep you safe.
-And if I come with you?

546
00:38:15,400 --> 00:38:17,400
Drowning, on the point of death.

547
00:38:20,320 --> 00:38:21,880
-I'm a nurse.
-What?

548
00:38:21,960 --> 00:38:24,160
-I can teach you how to save me.
-Whoa, hold on.

549
00:38:24,240 --> 00:38:25,880
I was drowning.
You just have to resuscitate me.

550
00:38:25,960 --> 00:38:27,040
'lust"?

551
00:38:27,120 --> 00:38:29,200
You've seen them do it loads of times
in films. CPR. The kiss of life.

552
00:38:29,280 --> 00:38:33,120
Rory, this isn't a film, okay?
What if I do it wrong?

553
00:38:33,200 --> 00:38:34,200
You won't.

554
00:38:35,280 --> 00:38:37,840
Okay. What if you don't
come back to life? What if...

555
00:38:37,920 --> 00:38:39,040
I trust you.

556
00:38:42,240 --> 00:38:46,160
What about him, hmm?
I mean, why do I have to be the one?

557
00:38:46,240 --> 00:38:48,560
Why do I have to save you?

558
00:38:49,440 --> 00:38:51,360
Because I know you'll never give up.

559
00:38:58,400 --> 00:39:00,680
We have to send this ship
back into space.

560
00:39:02,000 --> 00:39:04,480
I mean, imagine if the siren got ashore.

561
00:39:04,560 --> 00:39:06,160
She would have to process
every injured human.

562
00:39:07,520 --> 00:39:09,000
What about Toby?

563
00:39:11,360 --> 00:39:12,640
I'm sorry.

564
00:39:13,720 --> 00:39:17,160
Typhoid fever. Once he returns,
it's only a matter of time.

565
00:39:19,800 --> 00:39:24,400
What if I stay with him, here?
The siren will look after him.

566
00:39:26,480 --> 00:39:27,600
I can't go back to England.

567
00:39:28,680 --> 00:39:31,280
And what home does he have now,
if not with me?

568
00:39:34,520 --> 00:39:35,920
Do you think you can sail this thing?

569
00:39:38,240 --> 00:39:40,080
Just point me to the atom accelerator.

570
00:39:40,160 --> 00:39:41,160
(LAUGHS)

571
00:39:46,200 --> 00:39:48,440
RORY: I know you can do this.

572
00:39:50,080 --> 00:39:52,440
Of course, if you muck it up
I am going to be really cross.

573
00:39:52,520 --> 00:39:53,560
And dead.

574
00:39:57,000 --> 00:39:58,520
I'll see you in a minute.

575
00:40:05,840 --> 00:40:06,840
(SENSOR BEEPING RAPIDLY)

576
00:40:25,560 --> 00:40:28,560
Come on. Come on, Rory.
Not here. Not this way. Not today!

577
00:40:35,640 --> 00:40:37,880
He trusted me.
He trusted me to save him.

578
00:40:37,960 --> 00:40:41,240
You still can. You can still do this.
He believes in you. Come on, Amy!

579
00:40:42,480 --> 00:40:43,760
Come on!

580
00:40:58,120 --> 00:41:00,920
Please, please, please wake up.

581
00:41:01,000 --> 00:41:02,920
Please wake up.

582
00:41:03,000 --> 00:41:04,400
Wake up, wake up!

583
00:41:13,960 --> 00:41:15,480
(AMY SOBBING)

584
00:41:38,120 --> 00:41:40,000
(COUGHING)

585
00:41:48,800 --> 00:41:49,800
Yes!

586
00:41:50,080 --> 00:41:51,560
(GASPING)

587
00:41:53,800 --> 00:41:54,880
Amy.

588
00:41:56,400 --> 00:41:58,080
Amy, you did it. You did it!

589
00:42:46,920 --> 00:42:49,640
I thought I was an excellent pirate.

590
00:42:49,720 --> 00:42:52,320
-I thought you were an excellent nurse.
-Easy, tiger.

591
00:42:53,320 --> 00:42:54,760
Goodnight, Doctor.

592
00:42:54,840 --> 00:42:56,200
Goodnight, Amelia.

593
00:42:57,320 --> 00:42:59,120
You only call me Amelia
when you're worrying about me.

594
00:43:00,120 --> 00:43:01,560
I always worry about you.

595
00:43:07,040 --> 00:43:08,320
Mutual.

596
00:43:10,320 --> 00:43:11,440
Go to bed, Pond.

597
00:43:15,640 --> 00:43:16,920
You can't tell him.

598
00:43:18,280 --> 00:43:19,720
It's his future.

599
00:43:24,160 --> 00:43:25,400
I know.

600
00:43:40,520 --> 00:43:42,120
DOCTOR: Oh, Amelia.

601
00:43:45,880 --> 00:43:47,360
I've got mail.

602
00:43:47,480 --> 00:43:49,520
There's a living Time Lord
still out there.

603
00:43:51,040 --> 00:43:52,320
The house? What's the house?

604
00:43:52,400 --> 00:43:55,800
We walk on his back,
breathe his air, eat his food...

605
00:43:55,880 --> 00:43:57,400
HOUSE: And do my will.

606
00:43:57,480 --> 00:43:59,680
The little boxes will make you angry.

607
00:44:00,640 --> 00:44:01,920
(SCREAMING)

608
00:44:02,000 --> 00:44:03,040
I feel like a nine-year-old

609
00:44:03,120 --> 00:44:04,560
trying to rebuild a motorbike
in his bedroom.

610
00:44:04,640 --> 00:44:06,240
You are not my mother.

611
00:44:06,640 --> 00:44:08,600
HOUSE: Why shouldn't
I just kill you now?

